	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Search your Claude Code sessions and resume one in your terminal.

Trigger Alfred and type:  cs   (optionally followed by search terms)

Search matches the session description, working directory, git branch and id;
if those don't match it also searches the full conversation body.

Actions on the highlighted result:
  ↵        Resume in terminal with --dangerously-skip-permissions
  ⌥ ↵      Resume WITHOUT the bypass flag
  ⌘ ↵      Open the session's working directory in your editor
  ⌃ ↵      Reveal the session .jsonl transcript in Finder
  ⇧ ↵      Quick Look the conversation
  fn ↵     Copy the resume command to the clipboard

Configure Workflow lets you choose the terminal (Warp / iTerm / Terminal /
Ghostty), tab vs window, your editor, extra claude flags, and full-text search.

Requirements: Claude Code CLI on PATH (or ~/.local/bin/claude); the chosen
terminal app. Ghostty uses keystroke automation and needs Accessibility access.</string>
